Info2: <<
Package: cl-portableaserve-%type_pkg[lisp]
Version: 1.2.35
Revision: 1
Description: Portable Common Lisp webserver
License: LGPL
Maintainer: Lars Rosengreen <lars@margay.org>

Type: lisp (openmcl sbcl)

Depends: %type_pkg[lisp], cl-ppcre-%type_pkg[lisp], cl-puri-%type_pkg[lisp]

Source: mirror:sourceforge:portableaserve/portableaserve-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: c7fc8af81f003c27ee7596f7fd2b242a

SourceDirectory: portableaserve

PatchScript: <<
  rm -Rf libs/cl-ppcre
  rm -Rf libs/cl-puri
<<

CompileScript: <<
  #! /bin/sh -ev
  cd aserve
  SYSTEM="aserve"
  %p/bin/%type_pkg[lisp] <<EOF
  (require :asdf)
  (load "$SYSTEM.asd")
  (asdf:oos 'asdf:compile-op '$SYSTEM)
  (quit)
  EOF
<<

InstallScript: <<
  #! /bin/sh -ev
  SYSTEM="aserve"
  LISP="%type_pkg[lisp]"
  install -d -m 755 %i/lib/common-lisp/%type_pkg[lisp]/systems
  install -d -m 755 %i/lib/common-lisp/%type_pkg[lisp]/source/$SYSTEM
  ln -s %p/lib/common-lisp/%type_pkg[lisp]/source/$SYSTEM/$SYSTEM.asd %i/lib/common-lisp/%type_pkg[lisp]/systems/$SYSTEM.asd
  cp -Rp * %i/lib/common-lisp/%type_pkg[lisp]/source/$SYSTEM
<<


DescDetail: << 
A free and portable Common Lisp Webserver.  Portable AllegroServe is a
variant of AllegroServe(tm) with an explicit emphasis on portability
between Lispsystems and Operating Systems.  
<<

DescUsage: <<
Stilll a little rough around the edges :)

%p --> where your fink installation is located (ie /sw)
%type_pkg[lisp] --> lisp implementation you are using (ie openmcl)

(require :asdf)
(pushnew #P"%p/lib/common-lisp/%type_pkg[lisp]/systems/" 
         asdf:*central-registry*)
(asdf:oos 'asdf:load-op 'aserve)
<<


Homepage: http://portableaserve.sourceforge.net/

<<
